ts=2026-06-27T09:40:58.502Z type=context scope=project content="Solo project by Bruno Costa Prado. Single `main` branch. No CI/CD, no linters, no pre-commit hooks, no GitHub Actions. Conventional commits: feat/fix/docs prefixes." tags=team,workflow,branching
ts=2026-06-27T09:40:59.948Z type=project-config scope=project content="Go 1.26.4 project. Fyne v2.7.4 GUI toolkit (requires CGO + gcc). External dependency: ffmpeg binary (optional bundled in ffmpeg/<os>-<arch>/). Build: `go build -o file_converter .`. Test: `go test ./core/ -v`. Run CLI: `./file_converter input.mp4 --preset \"Fast 1080p\"`. Run GUI: `./file_converter` (no args)." tags=build,test,stack
ts=2026-06-27T09:41:01.542Z type=architecture scope=project content="Three-layer architecture: main.go (entry/routing), core/ (pure logic, no GUI), gui/ (Fyne views depend on core). Data flow: Preset → BuildFfmpegArgs → []string → Runner.Run (exec.Command) → stderr scan → onProgress callback. core/ splits into data (types.go, settings.go, preset.go), pipeline (ffmpeg.go, convert.go, runner.go), concurrency (queue.go, worker.go). gui/ has 5 panels loosely coupled via App controller." tags=layers,data-flow
ts=2026-06-27T09:41:03.149Z type=architecture scope=project content="Key architectural patterns: (1) Preset as Strategy — Preset struct holds encoding params, BuildFfmpegArgs interprets them as ffmpeg flags, new presets = new data not new code. (2) Worker Pool — N goroutines pull from mutex-guarded Queue with context cancellation. (3) Crash Recovery — Queue serialized to queue.json, loaded on GUI start, running items reset to pending. (4) HWAccelOverride — Preset.HWAccel maps to hardware encoder names, skips -preset and -crf for HW encoders. (5) AutoBitrateDetect — ffprobe probes source bitrate when HW encoding without explicit --bitrate." tags=patterns,design
ts=2026-06-27T09:41:04.515Z type=project-config scope=project content="CLI flags: --preset (default \"Fast 1080p\"), --output (\"./output\"), --ffmpeg-path (\"\"), --hwaccel (nvenc/qsv/amd/videotoolbox), --bitrate (e.g. \"2M\"), --keep-format (bool), --queue (JSON stdin), --concurrent (default 2), --version. Queue mode: `echo '[{\"InputPath\":\"a.mp4\",\"PresetName\":\"Fast 1080p\"}]' | file_converter --queue`." tags=cli,flags
ts=2026-06-27T09:41:06.113Z type=learned-pattern scope=project content="6 built-in presets: Fast 1080p (h264/aac/CRF23/medium/1920x1080, mp4), Small 720p (h264/aac/CRF28/fast/1280x720, mp4), H265 Compact (h265/aac/CRF28, mkv), Lossless (h264/copy/CRF0/slow, mkv), Audio Only (copy/aac/192k, m4a), Copy Stream (copy/copy, mkv). Preset.HWAccel field overrides video encoder to hardware variant when non-empty." tags=presets,encoding
ts=2026-06-27T09:41:07.615Z type=error-solution scope=project content="HW encoders (nvenc/qsv/amd/videotoolbox) reject ffmpeg -preset and -crf flags. Fix: BuildFfmpegArgs skips -preset and -crf when Preset.HWAccel != \"\". HW encoders require -b:v instead for quality control. Fix implements: if bitrate string is non-empty, use -b:v; if empty and HWAccel set, call ProbeVideoBitrate for auto-detect." tags=hwaccel,ffmpeg,gpu
ts=2026-06-27T09:41:09.054Z type=error-solution scope=project content="Fyne UI updates from non-main goroutines (e.g. progress callbacks from WorkerPool) must use fyne.Do() for thread safety. Fix: QueuePanel.UpdateProgress wraps p.list.Refresh in fyne.Do. Similarly, app.NewWithID is required instead of app.New for persistent settings across sessions." tags=fyne,threading,gui
ts=2026-06-27T09:41:10.856Z type=learned-pattern scope=project content="FFmpeg binary resolution priority: (1) user-provided --ffmpeg-path flag, (2) bundled binary in ffmpeg/<os>-<arch>/ next to executable, (3) system PATH via exec.LookPath. FfmpegPaths returns bundled dir candidates. FindFfmpeg iterates each dir checking \"ffmpeg\" and \"ffmpeg.exe\", then falls back to PATH. ProbeVideoBitrate derives ffprobe path from ffmpeg path (same dir, same base name with \"probe\" suffix), falls back to PATH." tags=ffmpeg,resolution,binary
ts=2026-06-27T09:41:12.098Z type=architecture scope=project content="Settings stored as JSON in platform config: Windows %APPDATA%/file_converter/settings.json, macOS ~/Library/Application Support/file_converter/settings.json, Linux ~/.config/file_converter/settings.json. Fields: ffmpeg_path, theme (system/light/dark), output_dir, default_preset, concurrent_jobs. Queue also persists as queue.json in same directory for crash recovery." tags=settings,persistence,paths
ts=2026-06-27T09:41:13.430Z type=learned-pattern scope=project content="Converter uses suffix \"k\" for bitrate values (e.g. \"2789k\") instead of \"M\" for precision. ProbeVideoBitrate divides raw bits by 1000 and appends \"k\". This avoids integer-truncation from dividing by 1,000,000 for \"M\" suffix. FFmpeg accepts both k and M suffixes." tags=bitrate,convention
